


Commands for Linux Distribution based on Arch Linux

sudo pacman -Syu
sudo pacman -S polybar
sudo pacman -S dmenu
sudo pacman -S rofi

.....

Commands for Linux Distribution based on Ubuntu or Debian

sudo apt-get update -y
sudo apt-get upgrade -y
sudo apt-get install -y dmenu
sudo apt-get install -y rofi

Now you need to install the polybar in your Distro based on Ubuntu or Debian:

Go to your home folder and open a new terminal window and execute these commands down below:

sudo apt-get install cmake cmake-data libcairo2-dev libxcb1-dev libxcb-ewmh-dev libxcb-icccm4-dev libxcb-image0-dev libxcb-randr0-dev libxcb-util0-dev libxcb-xkb-dev pkg-config python-xcbgen xcb-proto libxcb-xrm-dev libasound2-dev libmpdclient-dev libiw-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev libpulse-dev libxcb-composite0-dev xcb libxcb-ewmh2

git clone https://github.com/jaagr/polybar.git && cd polybar && sudo ./build.sh


